<span id="freeTextContainer1499016220459688679">I would describe this as women&apos;s fiction, set on the Italian island of Sardinia at the end of WW2. A young woman with a fiancé has her simple life turned upside down by the arrival of American forces. As she has been dressmaking for English-speaking residents, she is called upon to act as translator. <br/><br/>Local food and drink, romances and jealousies, conventions and contrasts. This is a richly woven tale steeped in the author&apos;s family background. <br/><br/>I downloaded an ARC from Net Galley. This is an unbia</span>
