        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1963379842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15167389628567713323">I listened to the audio version of this book, beautifully narrated by the author. Filled with luscious - almost cinematic - descriptions of family feasts and simple picnics, country festivals and rituals, vineyards and seacoasts, the story of Carmela sometimes takes a back seat to post-war Sardinian village life. A farm girl and apprentice dressmaker, Carmela learns enough English as a summer housemaid to British families that she is tapped as interpreter to an American lieutenant on the local m</span>
  <span id="freeText15167389628567713323" style="display:none">I listened to the audio version of this book, beautifully narrated by the author. Filled with luscious - almost cinematic - descriptions of family feasts and simple picnics, country festivals and rituals, vineyards and seacoasts, the story of Carmela sometimes takes a back seat to post-war Sardinian village life. A farm girl and apprentice dressmaker, Carmela learns enough English as a summer housemaid to British families that she is tapped as interpreter to an American lieutenant on the local military base. Her eyes open to the possibilities beyond marriage and motherhood forever in her village, and her internal conflict grows stronger and more disruptive until the novel's tragic climax. <br />One can forgive the author for the improbable coincidence that ties all the loose ends together because the setting is so vividly drawn.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15167389628567713323" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

