<div id="review_2172302345" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2172302345" />
    <a title="Jo Fetsco" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38804016-jo-fetsco"><img alt="Jo Fetsco" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2172302345?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jo Fetsco" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jo Fetsco" href="/user/show/38804016-jo-fetsco">Jo Fetsco</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2172302345" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5513105314159436961">Mina is a London-based travel journalist who is back in Sardinia to attend a relative’s funeral.  While there, she becomes obsessed with finding out what happened to her aunt Carmela, who was engaged to a fellow Sardinian, but fell in love with a sergeant in the American Army in 1952 while working as his translator.  It is a very well-told, well-detailed love story and mystery with themes of hope, sacrifice, and extraordinary love.  The author, who is also the reader of this audio book and does </span>
  <span id="freeText5513105314159436961" style="display:none">Mina is a London-based travel journalist who is back in Sardinia to attend a relative’s funeral.  While there, she becomes obsessed with finding out what happened to her aunt Carmela, who was engaged to a fellow Sardinian, but fell in love with a sergeant in the American Army in 1952 while working as his translator.  It is a very well-told, well-detailed love story and mystery with themes of hope, sacrifice, and extraordinary love.  The author, who is also the reader of this audio book and does a great job with the reading, uses wonderful language and imagery and paints a beautiful picture of Sardinia and Italian life, food, and culture.  </span>
  <a data-text-id="5513105314159436961" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


